gomodel:SYNGO_5525  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Angiomotin colocalizes with PSD-95 (Fig. 1F); it is present in the highly enriched PSD fraction (Fig. 1E) and coIPs with PSD-95 and MUPP1/MPDZ (Fig 1G-I); Fig. 2 provides evidence that over-expressed YFP-tagged AMOT co-distributes with the presynaptic marker Bassoon and the excitatory postsynaptic markers PSD-95 and Mupp1, but not with the inhibitory postsynaptic marker Gephyrin.. Experimental description: \"Dissociated cultures of primary hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 Sprague-Dawley rat embryos...\" (p. 726)\nA commercial antibody (C-18) was tested for its specificity to detect AMOT, but not the related gene products AMOT-L1 or AMOT-L2 in transfected HEK293T cells (Fig. 1 A,B).\nAnother antibody (#2095) generated against the N-Terminus recognizes specifically AMOT-130 and not the AMOT-80 splice isoform.\nReviewed UniProt-Accs are only available for Human (Q4VCS5) and Mouse (Q8VHG2)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5525" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

